{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"16372","heading":"Determination of eligibility and project selection","label":"16372 Determination of eligibility and project selection","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch149/schIX/ptJ","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe National Environmental Policy Act of 1969, referred to in subsec. (d)(2), is , , , which is classified generally to chapter 55 (§ 4321 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 91–19083 Stat. 852section 4321 of this titleJan. 1, 1970","Prior ProvisionsA prior section 16372, , , , related to administration of the program under former part J, prior to repeal by , , .Pub. L. 109–58, title IX, § 999B119 Stat. 917Pub. L. 113–67, div. A, title III, § 301(a)127 Stat. 1181Aug. 8, 2005Dec. 26, 2013","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Wage Rate RequirementsFor provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of , including authority of Secretary of Labor, see .Pub. L. 117–58section 18851 of this title"],"amendments":["References in TextThe National Environmental Policy Act of 1969, referred to in subsec. (d)(2), is , , , which is classified generally to chapter 55 (§ 4321 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 91–19083 Stat. 852section 4321 of this titleJan. 1, 1970","Prior ProvisionsA prior section 16372, , , , related to administration of the program under former part J, prior to repeal by , , .Pub. L. 109–58, title IX, § 999B119 Stat. 917Pub. L. 113–67, div. A, title III, § 301(a)127 Stat. 1181Aug. 8, 2005Dec. 26, 2013","Wage Rate RequirementsFor provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of , including authority of Secretary of Labor, see .Pub. L. 117–58section 18851 of this title"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Establishment of program","label":"a Establishment of program","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a Federal credit instrument under ;section 16373 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a grant under ; orsection 16374 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"both a Federal credit instrument and a grant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Eligibility","label":"b Eligibility","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the entity proposing to carry out the project submits a letter of interest prior to submission of an application under paragraph (3) for the project; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the project meets the criteria described in this subsection.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Creditworthiness","label":"2 Creditworthiness","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Each project and obligor that receives a Federal credit instrument or a grant under the CIFIA program shall be creditworthy, such that there exists a reasonable prospect of repayment of the principal and interest on the Federal credit instrument, as determined by the Secretary under subparagraph (B).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Reasonable prospect of repayment","label":"B Reasonable prospect of repayment","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the strength of the contractual terms of an eligible project (if available for the applicable market segment);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the forecast of noncontractual cash flows supported by market projections from reputable sources, as determined by the Secretary, and cash sweeps or other structural enhancements;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/iii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fiii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"at the time of loan close; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/iii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fiii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"throughout the loan term, including after the project is completed;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the financial strength of the investors and strategic partners of the obligor, if applicable; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other financial metrics and analyses that are relied on by the private lending community and nationally recognized credit rating agencies, as determined appropriate by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Applications","label":"3 Applications","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To be eligible for assistance under the CIFIA program, an obligor shall submit to the Secretary a project application at such time, in such manner, and containing such information as the Secretary determines to be appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Eligible project costs","label":"4 Eligible project costs","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A project under the CIFIA program shall have eligible project costs that are reasonably anticipated to equal or exceed $100,000,000.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Revenue sources","label":"5 Revenue sources","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F5%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"user fees;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F5%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"payments owing to the obligor under a public-private partnership; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F5%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other revenue sources that also secure or fund the project obligations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":"Obligor will be identified later","label":"6 Obligor will be identified later","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the obligor; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identified at a later date through completion of a procurement and selection of the private party.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":"Beneficial effects","label":"7 Beneficial effects","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"attract public or private investment for the project; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enable the project to proceed at an earlier date than the project would otherwise be able to proceed or reduce the lifecycle costs (including debt service costs) of the project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":"Project readiness","label":"8 Project readiness","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fb%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To be eligible for assistance under the CIFIA program, the applicant shall demonstrate a reasonable expectation that the contracting process for construction of the project can commence by not later than 90 days after the date on which a Federal credit instrument or grant is obligated for the project under the CIFIA program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Selection among eligible projects","label":"c Selection among eligible projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Establishment of application process","label":"1 Establishment of application process","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"receive credit assistance on terms acceptable to the Secretary, if adequate funds are available (including any funds provided on behalf of an eligible project under paragraph (3)(B)(ii)) to cover the subsidy amount associated with the Federal credit instrument; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"adequate funds are available to cover the amount of the grant; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Secretary determines that the project is eligible under subsection (b).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Priority","label":"2 Priority","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"are large-capacity, common carrier infrastructure;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"have demonstrated demand for use of the infrastructure by associated projects that capture carbon dioxide from anthropogenic sources or ambient air;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enable geographical diversity in associated projects that capture carbon dioxide from anthropogenic sources or ambient air, with the goal of enabling projects in all major carbon dioxide-emitting regions of the United States; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"are sited within, or adjacent to, existing pipeline or other linear infrastructure corridors, in a manner that minimizes environmental disturbance and other siting concerns.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Master credit agreements","label":"3 Master credit agreements","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Priority projects","label":"A Priority projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FA%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"additional commitments from associated carbon capture projects to use the project; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FA%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"all necessary permits and approvals; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is a project of high priority, as determined in accordance with the criteria described in paragraph (2).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Adequate funding not available","label":"B Adequate funding not available","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to enter into a master credit agreement in lieu of the Federal credit instrument; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to wait to execute a Federal credit instrument until the fiscal year for which additional funds are available to receive credit assistance; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if the lack of adequate funding is solely with respect to amounts available for the subsidy amount, to pay the subsidy amount to fund the Federal credit instrument.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Federal requirements","label":"d Federal requirements","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Nothing in this part supersedes the applicability of any other requirement under Federal law (including regulations).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"NEPA","label":"2 NEPA","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Federal credit assistance may only be provided under this part for a project that has received an environmental categorical exclusion, a finding of no significant impact, or a record of decision under the National Environmental Policy Act of 1969 ( et seq.).42 U.S.C. 4321","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Use of American iron, steel, and manufactured goods","label":"e Use of American iron, steel, and manufactured goods","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), no Federal credit instrument or grant provided under the CIFIA program shall be made available for a project unless all iron, steel, and manufactured goods used in the project are produced in the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Exceptions","label":"2 Exceptions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the application would be inconsistent with the public interest;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"iron, steel, or a relevant manufactured good is not produced in the United States in sufficient and reasonably available quantity, or of a satisfactory quality; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the inclusion of iron, steel, or a manufactured good produced in the United States will increase the cost of the overall project by more than 25 percent.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Waivers","label":"3 Waivers","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"on an informal basis; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"by electronic means, including on the official public website of the Department;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"allow for informal public comment relating to the request for not fewer than 15 days before making a determination with respect to the request; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"approve or disapprove the request by not later than the date that is 120 days after the date of receipt of the request.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Applicability","label":"4 Applicability","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fe%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"This subsection shall be applied in accordance with any applicable obligations of the United States under international agreements.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Application processing procedures","label":"f Application processing procedures","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Notice of complete application","label":"1 Notice of complete application","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Ff%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the application is complete; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Ff%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"additional information or materials are needed to complete the application.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Approval or denial of application","label":"2 Approval or denial of application","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 60 days after the date of issuance of a written notice under paragraph (1), the Secretary shall provide to the applicant a written notice informing the applicant whether the Secretary has approved or disapproved the application.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Development-phase activities","label":"g Development-phase activities","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16372","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16372%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any Federal credit instrument provided under the CIFIA program may be used to finance up to 100 percent of the cost of development-phase activities, as described in .section 16371(4)(A) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
